sec.p:
The transfer function of the first stage (voltage loop gain) for this system is described by Equation (1) and the step response of the voltage loop is given by Figure 9.
\begin{equation*}
\frac{V_{o}(s)}{d(s)}=\frac{31850 s+318733}{s^{2}+1785.7 s} \tag{1}
\end{equation*}

The transfer function of the second stage (Battery Current Control Loop) for this system is described by Equation (2) and the step response of the battery current control loop) is given by Figure 10.
\begin{equation*}
\frac{V_{o}(s)}{d(s)}=\frac{1.566}{s+1.755} \tag{2}
\end{equation*}

The transfer function of the third stage (Inductor Current Control Loop) for this system is described by Equation (3) and the step response of the inductor current control loop) is given by Figure 11.
\begin{equation*}
\frac{V_{o}(s)}{d(s)}=\frac{325000}{s^{2}+102400 s} \tag{3}
\end{equation*}
